					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Imagine playing a FFIV midi and it sounding just like FFIV. Or Beethoven with FFVI instruments. Yes, I know this is somewhat possible with soundfonts... but the results are not particularly striking.
<br />
<br />How much work would it be to code an SPC core as a Windows MIDI interface driver? I imagine it would involve intercepting MIDI OUT messages; processing/mixing them with the DSP simulation code; and sending the mix to the WAVE OUT driver. The actual SPC700 implementation would be unneeded; only the samples and especially, the DSP-based modulation and filtering would have to be figured in.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

